So the bait will take, I hope;
(aside)
why, my Lord, I imagine Lady Charlotte's good-nature, here got the better of her judgement; I have heard her profess a strict friendship for Emmeline; besides, your Lordship knows that beauty is not a recommendation of one female to another.

Then all my fears are true;
(aside)
but suppose, Sir, my sister's affection should have been seriously engaged.
